curam.util.client.domain.convert.ClientDomainConverter, DomainConverter, DomainPlugIn, PlugIn
public class SvrInt16BareConverter
extends SvrInt16Converter

Converter for the SVR_INT16 domain that formats and parses values in a non-locale-specific manner. This may be used for internal identifiers, as these values are not displayed on the pages and are used mostly as parameter values. The formatter does not use a grouping (e.g., thousands) separator character and the parser always expects the minus sign to be on the left of the number.

format

public java.lang.String format(java.lang.Object data)
Formats a number without grouping separator characters and, for negative numbers, places the minus sign on the left. This relies on the basic behavior of the java.util.Short.toString method.

Specified by:
format in interface DomainConverter
Overrides:

parse

public java.lang.Object parse(java.lang.String data)
                       throws ConversionException
Parses a number. The number should not contain grouping separator characters or a decimal point. For negative numbers, the minus sign should be on the left, regardless of the locale. This relies on the basic behavior of the java.util.Short.valueOf(String) method.

Specified by:
